    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for firefox.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Mozilla Firefox is an open-source web browser, designed for standards compliance, performance, and portability.\n\nThis update upgrades Firefox to version 102.3.0 ESR.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* expat: a use-after-free in the doContent function in xmlparse.c (CVE-2022-40674)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
